```

#include <kipr/wombat.h>

int main()
{
    create_connect();
    wait_for_light(5);
    shut_down_in(119);

    create_drive_direct(150,-150);
    msleep(1000);
    create_drive_direct(200,300);
    msleep(3000);
    create_drive_direct(-200,200);
    msleep(1000);
    create_drive_direct(200,200);
    msleep(6000);
    create_drive_direct(150,150);
    msleep(4000);
    create_drive_direct(200,1);
    msleep(15000);


    create_stop();
    create_disconnect();
    return 0;

}

@everyone The PVC cuts in the Fall Game Table include all the cuts for the PVC that will be in the Spring competition. However not all the pieces in those cuts are included in the Fall Game Table build and a full version will be released like normal at the start of the Botball season. There will be a few additional pieces besides PVC that will be added as well when the full version is released but those have not been finalized yet.

The Fall Game Table is a half table similar to one for the competition that teams can use to train on this fall. KIPR will not be hosting a competition this fall, however if teams decide to get together and host a skirmish, virtually or in person. We will try to support these if we can, however the fall is a busy time for prep for us and so our availability will be dependent on that. If you need help with documents for organizing a skirmish or brackets or similar we can definitely help with those.

Teams that have already registered and had parts of their kits sent to them will have received some of the game pieces for this year and good things to do on this table may be to practice making things to pick up those pieces or methods of sorting them or stacking.

